body_html:
Thanks to @easyhangul, that was the problem! I followed the instructions to upgrade my TensorFlow installation, and then import_pb_to_tensorboard.py worked successfully!

Enhancement suggestion: it would be great if the Python tools could check that the local installation of TensorFlow is at the required minimum version. The error returned here is not very user-friendly.

STEPS TO FIX

I had to upgrade pip from 8.1.2 to 9.0.1, then I ran pip install --upgrade tensorflow.

Now I'm running v1.3.0:

$ python -c "import tensorflow as tf; print(tf.GIT_VERSION, tf.VERSION)"
('v1.3.0-rc2-20-g0787eee', '1.3.0')

...and import_pb_to_tensorboard.py appears to run successfully:

$ python import_pb_to_tensorboard.py --model_dir ~/Code/AndroidTensorFlowMNISTExample-daj/model/mnist_model_graph.pb --log_dir /tmp/tensorflow_logdir
<warnings snipped>
Model Imported. Visualize by running: > tensorboard --logdir=/tmp/tensorflow_logdir

I can now see something in my TensorBoard (double clicking on the "import" blob reveals the whole graph):

body:
Thanks to @easyhangul, that was the problem!  I followed [the instructions to upgrade my TensorFlow](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_mac) installation, and then  `import_pb_to_tensorboard.py` worked successfully!

Enhancement suggestion: it would be great if the Python tools could check that the local installation of TensorFlow is at the required minimum version.  The error returned here is not very user-friendly.

**STEPS TO FIX**

I had to upgrade `pip` from 8.1.2 to 9.0.1, then I ran `pip install --upgrade tensorflow`.

Now I'm running v1.3.0:
```
$ python -c "import tensorflow as tf; print(tf.GIT_VERSION, tf.VERSION)"
('v1.3.0-rc2-20-g0787eee', '1.3.0')
```
...and `import_pb_to_tensorboard.py` appears to run successfully:

```
$ python import_pb_to_tensorboard.py --model_dir ~/Code/AndroidTensorFlowMNISTExample-daj/model/mnist_model_graph.pb --log_dir /tmp/tensorflow_logdir
<warnings snipped>
Model Imported. Visualize by running: > tensorboard --logdir=/tmp/tensorflow_logdir
```
I can now see something in my TensorBoard (double clicking on the "import" blob reveals the whole graph):

![screen shot 2017-08-27 at 3 38 51 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/739125/29753357-e76cd524-8b3d-11e7-8dd4-e8a7062dada9.png)
